# Rest APIs

## Table of Contents

1. [Folder Structure](#folder-structure)
2. [Installation](#installation)

## Folder Structure

.
├── src/ # Source files
│ ├── app.ts # Main application entry point
│ ├── controllers/ # controllers files
| ├──
│ ├── routes/ # Route files
│ │ ├── feed.ts # Main router file (e.g., for express.js)
│ │ ├── users.ts # Route file for user-related routes
│ │ └── ... # Other route files
│ └── ... # Other source files
├── dist/ # Automated tests
│ ├── unit/ # Route files
│ └── routes/ # Integration tests
├── node_modules/ # Installed packages
├── .gitignore # Specifies intentionally untracked files to ignore
├── package.json # Defines npm package dependencies and scripts
├── tsconfig.json # Configuration for TypeScript
└── README.md # The file you are reading

## Installation

```bash
npm install express
# implementing validation in nodeJS app
npm install --save express-validator
npm install --save-dev @types/express-validator
# install mongoose to connect to mongoDB
npm install mongoose

# install multer for handling multipart/form-data, which is primarily used for uploading files
npm install --save multer
npm install --save-dev @types/multer










